Ex. No:  — Perform Data Selection and Slicing in Pandas DataFrame
Aim

To perform data selection and slicing operations in Pandas DataFrame.

Theory

Selection and slicing help retrieve specific rows and columns from a dataset for analysis.


Software / Tools Required
•
Python 3.x
•
Anaconda Distribution
•
Jupyter Notebook / IDLE / Google Colab
•
Pandas Library



Program
import pandas as pd

# Creating DataFrame
data = {
    'Name': ['Ravi', 'Anu', 'Kumar', 'Divya', 'Arun'],
    'Department': ['AI&DS', 'CSE', 'AI&DS', 'ECE', 'AI&DS'],
    'Marks': [88, 92, 79, 85, 90]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

print("Complete DataFrame:")
print(df)

# Single column
print("\nMarks Column:")
print(df['Marks'])

# Multiple columns
print("\nName and Marks:")
print(df[['Name', 'Marks']])

# Row slicing
print("\nFirst Three Rows:")
print(df[0:3])

# loc
print("\nUsing loc:")
print(df.loc[1:3, ['Name', 'Marks']])

# iloc
print("\nUsing iloc:")
print(df.iloc[0:3, [0, 2]])

# Conditional filtering
print("\nMarks > 85:")
print(df[df['Marks'] > 85])



Procedure
Import Pandas library.
Create a DataFrame.
Display complete dataset.
Select single column.
Select multiple columns.
Slice rows using indexes.
Use loc for label indexing.
Use iloc for position indexing.
Apply conditional filtering.
Execute and verify output.



